From: NuttX P2 port <dev@nuttx.apache.org>
Subject: [PATCH] newlib libm: remove unused cdefs includes from cproj

The RCSID uses in these files are already commented out, leaving the NetBSD
sys/cdefs.h dependency unused.  NuttX intentionally supplies its own system
headers while embedding Newlib libm.

--- newlib/newlib/newlib/libm/complex/cproj.c
+++ newlib/newlib/newlib/libm/complex/cproj.c
@@ -71 +70,0 @@ QUICKREF
-#include <sys/cdefs.h>
--- newlib/newlib/newlib/libm/complex/cprojf.c
+++ newlib/newlib/newlib/libm/complex/cprojf.c
@@ -32 +31,0 @@
-#include <sys/cdefs.h>
